Header: North Korea’s Kim Jong Un returns to Pyongyang after summit
Content: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un returned to Pyongyang after visiting Hanoi for the second summit with U.S. President Donald Trump.The North’s official news agency KCNA released still photographs of Kim arriving at Pyongyang Railway Station and being welcomed by North Korean officials and residents.KCNA said Kim successfully finished his official goodwill visit to Vietnam and arrived in Pyongyang at around 0300 a.m.Kim was in Hanoi for a second meeting with Trump which was cut short after they failed to reach a deal on the extent of sanctions relief North Korea would get in exchange for steps to give up its nuclear programme.
